# Ito Backend Configuration Guide

This guide covers the multi-tenant backend server and client configuration for Ito.

## Architecture Overview

The Ito backend is a multi-tenant HTTP API that serves project data for
`{org}/{repo}` namespaces. All project-scoped routes are nested under:

```
/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/...
```

A single server instance can serve many projects without requiring individual
git checkouts.

## Client Configuration (`backend` section in `ito.json`)

Enable backend mode in your project config:

```json
{
  "backend": {
    "enabled": true,
    "url": "http://127.0.0.1:9010",
    "token": null,
    "tokenEnvVar": "ITO_BACKEND_TOKEN",
    "project": {
      "org": "my-org",
      "repo": "my-repo"
    },
    "timeoutMs": 30000,
    "maxRetries": 3
  }
}
```

### Key Fields

| Field | Description | Default |
|-------|-------------|---------|
| `enabled` | Enable backend API integration | `false` |
| `url` | Base URL for the backend server | `http://127.0.0.1:9010` |
| `token` | Explicit bearer token (overrides env var) | `null` |
| `tokenEnvVar` | Env var name holding the bearer token | `ITO_BACKEND_TOKEN` |
| `project.org` | Organization namespace for routing | _(required when enabled)_ |
| `project.repo` | Repository namespace for routing | _(required when enabled)_ |
| `timeoutMs` | Request timeout in milliseconds | `30000` |
| `maxRetries` | Retry attempts for transient failures | `3` |

### Environment Variable Overrides

Project namespace can be overridden via environment variables:

- `ITO_BACKEND_PROJECT_ORG` â€” overrides `project.org`
- `ITO_BACKEND_PROJECT_REPO` â€” overrides `project.repo`

Config values take precedence over environment variables.

## Server Configuration (`server` section)

The server config is used when running `ito serve`:

```json
{
  "server": {
    "enabled": true,
    "bind": "127.0.0.1",
    "port": 9010,
    "dataDir": "/path/to/data",
    "storage": {
      "kind": "filesystem"
    },
    "auth": {
      "adminTokens": ["<admin-token>"],
      "tokenSeed": "<secret-seed>"
    },
    "allowed": {
      "orgs": ["my-org"],
      "repos": {
        "my-org": "*"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Storage Backends

- **`filesystem`** (default): Stores project data as markdown files under `{dataDir}/projects/{org}/{repo}/.ito/`
- **`sqlite`**: Proof-of-concept SQLite-backed storage (single database, keyed by org/repo)

### Authentication Model

The backend uses a two-tier token model:

1. **Admin tokens** â€” Full access to any project. Listed in `auth.adminTokens`.
2. **Derived project tokens** â€” Scoped to a single `{org}/{repo}`. Computed as `HMAC-SHA256(tokenSeed, "{org}/{repo}")`.

Clients typically use derived tokens. Admin tokens are for operators and CI.

### Allowlist Enforcement

Requests to non-allowlisted org/repo pairs are rejected with HTTP 403,
even with a valid admin token. Configure via:

- `allowed.orgs` â€” list of permitted organizations
- `allowed.repos` â€” per-org policies: `"*"` (all repos) or a list of specific repos

## API Endpoints

All project-scoped endpoints require authentication.

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/v1/health` | Health check (unauthenticated) |
| GET | `/api/v1/ready` | Readiness check (unauthenticated) |
| GET | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/changes` | List changes |
| GET | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/changes/{id}` | Get change details |
| GET | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/changes/{id}/sync` | Pull change artifacts |
| POST | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/changes/{id}/sync` | Push change artifacts |
| POST | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/changes/{id}/archive` | Archive a change and mirror promoted specs |
| GET | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/changes/{id}/tasks` | Get change tasks |
| GET | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/modules` | List modules |
| GET | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/modules/{id}` | Get module details |
| GET | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/specs` | List promoted specs |
| GET | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/specs/{id}` | Get promoted spec markdown |
| POST | `/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/events` | Ingest audit events |

## Remote Agent Workflow

When backend mode is enabled, treat the CLI as the primary interface for active work.

- Local `.ito/changes/*` and `.ito/specs/*` content may be absent by design; do not create markdown manually to compensate.
- Use `ito show <change-or-spec>` and `ito show specs` for reads.
- Use `ito tasks ...` for task mutations and `ito tasks sync pull <change-id>` when you need a local working copy for grep/diff.
- Use `ito archive <change-id>` to promote specs and archive changes; this updates both the backend mirror and local Git projection.
- Treat Git-projected files as scan/backup surfaces, not the source of truth for active mutations.

## Event Forwarding

When backend mode is enabled, the CLI automatically forwards local audit
events to the backend after each command. Events are sent to:

```
POST {url}/api/v1/projects/{org}/{repo}/events
```

Forwarding is best-effort and never affects command outcome.

## Running the Server

```bash
ito serve --data-dir /path/to/data --admin-token <token> --token-seed <seed> --allow-org my-org
```

Or with a config file that has the `server` section configured:

```bash
ito serve
```
